<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880623-0055 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Allied Group Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ALGR </CO><IN> BBK </IN><TEXT>   Allied Group Inc. said its board authorized the purchase of as much as $1 million of its common stock on the open market from time to time over the next year.    The Des Moines, Iowa, insurance holding company, which has about 6.8 million common shares outstanding, said the repurchased shares will be held as treasury shares.    Allied said the program isn't in response to any tender offer or any other offer for the company's shares. In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Allied closed at $11.25, unchanged. </TEXT></DOC>